##Popular Science, refuting rumors... on the battlefield of anti-epidemic, what can Internet medicine do

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

The following article is from the eight-point Health News Plus by Guan Qi

Eight o'clock health news Semicolon, good health business report.

In the face of a sudden outbreak, Internet medicine can do a lot.

Seventeen years ago in the SARS epidemic, smoking, iodized salt can prevent "SARS" and other rumors, once to the people of the country has brought great trouble.

Seventeen years later, when the new coronavirus hit, a rapid build up of information channels allowed people who had fled the outbreak at home to access reliable information about the outbreak and avoid being misled by rumors. To prevent garlic sterilization, fumigation vinegar disinfection, Banlangen Prevention, such as "confused behavior" return.

Comparing the SARS and new coronavirus outbreaks 17 years apart, in addition to the experience left over from SARS, the protective mechanism, and the continuously developing capabilities of medical research, diagnosis and treatment, the war against the plague also added a new power to the Internet.

As of 2400 hours on February 7,31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps have reported a total of 31,774 confirmed cases (including 6,101 severe cases) , a total of 2,050 cured and discharged from hospitals, and a total of 722 deaths, a total of 34,546 confirmed cases (14 nuclear reductions in Heilongjiang) and 27,657 suspected cases have been reported. A total of 345498 close contacts were traced and 189660 close contacts remained under medical observation.

At the same time, in order to prevent further large-scale spread of the epidemic, Harbin, Nanjing, Ningbo, Fuzhou, Linyi, Hangzhou and other cities have announced the implementation of closed management of all village units; In principle, one person from each family goes out every two days to purchase living materials.

When isolation is the best way to prevent and control an epidemic, when people have to stop going out and partying unnecessarily, the Internet has become the bottom line demand of the general population.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Delta image by yestone

Tencent medical officials said that in the face of sudden outbreaks, the Internet, especially Internet medicine, has greater value: first, it can quickly spread information about the epidemic, and speed up the response speed of every individual in the whole society, in a short time, it calls for the mobilization and participation of every person in the whole society; secondly, it can quickly popularize scientific protection knowledge and enhance the ability of the whole People's protection; thirdly, it can provide highly effective self-examination and on-line consultation service, effectively triage non-new coronary pneumonia patients to relieve the pressure of off-line hospitals.

Let the message get out in time, let the rumor mill run free

Li Ming (not his real name) , who lives in Songbei District, Harbin, has just received a bottle of rubbing alcohol from the community, with instructions on the bottle to sterilise it with high levels of alcohol.

Li Ming didn't panic, even though he'd been cooped up for days.

"when SARS happened, I was still in primary school. In my memory, the school was disinfected with vinegar and the room smelled like vinegar. I didn't understand until I grew up that it was useless to disinfect with vinegar. "

After getting the rubbing alcohol, Li Ming said, it's easy to get authoritative information now, and rumors can be quickly dispelled. In the mobile phone, some authoritative wechat public accounts and APPS will release a lot of epidemic information in a timely manner. Community workers will release photos of each floor disinfection through the owner's wechat group every day, and keep everyone abreast of all kinds of epidemic prevention information. On TV, the news is updated every day, and experts are on hand to explain how to prevent the disease.

"A few days ago, there was an online rumor that Shuanghuanglian can prevent new coronavirus. Before I went out to buy it, some experts had already refuted the rumor on the Internet, " Li Ming said.

In the midst of a raging epidemic, fragmented sources of information are leading to panic, fueled by rumors or pseudo scientific treatments that are holding back a national war of resistance. In addition to the lack of medical supplies to support, the COVID-19 epidemic prevention and control progress so far, the main battlefield at the grass-roots level, and grass-roots focus on population screening, epidemic prevention and control of Education is particularly urgent.

On January 26, the National Health Commission issued a notice on strengthening the prevention and control of pneumonia in primary medical and health institutions, which was issued by the COVID-19. The circular pointed out that primary medical and health institutions should make full use of information technology to carry out epidemic prevention and control, and can accurately and timely disseminate epidemic prevention and control and health education information to residents in their districts by means of telephone and intelligent voice reminders.

The Internet health platform is also playing an active role in helping the government to educate the public about the epidemic. Tencent medical code, micro medical, good doctors and other vertical medical platforms, have set up popular science columns, remove the public knowledge blind spot, to help people more rational and objective view of the COVID-19 infection of pneumonia.

Take tencent as an example. At the beginning of the outbreak, wechat's "payment" page launched a "medical health" service for users across the country. Through this entrance, you can open the "tencent health" applet, enter the "national dynamics of new pneumonia epidemic" zone. The special area not only includes authoritative medical science knowledge, but also provides authoritative 24-hour real-time epidemic statistics and fever clinic functions from the National Health Commission.

Medical Health section of wechat payment page can be entered into the "national new pneumonia epidemic dynamics" zone.

Among them, the popular science content is supported by the popular science content from the official channels of the China Center for Disease Control and Prevention and the China population publicity and education center of the National Health Commission, and is coordinated by 100 experts from tencent medical code, to text, video, live broadcast and other ways to produce.

It is understood that tencent medical code also systematizes relevant knowledge into prevention guidelines, examination and diagnosis, and knowledge of different stages of treatment progress in the "national new type of pneumonia real-time Popular Science Survey" special area, and distinguish hot science popularization, refuting rumors, for the elderly / Young / pregnant groups of expertise and self-examination of diseases, so as to make it easy for users to get targeted disease knowledge one-stop.

In order to let people who need to see a doctor find the right hospital in the first place, tencent health, wechat team, tencent maps, tencent news and many other teams within tencent are working together under the guidance of the Publicity Department of the National Health Commission, with first-hand authority outpatient service information, publish"countrywide fevers outpatient service map"quickly. As of February 4, the map had covered 357 cities and could be consulted for more than 12,000 hospitals, including 11,637 fever outpatient hospitals and 1,960 designated hospitals for medical treatment. With the upgrade to version 2.0, users will also be able to view real time details of some hospitals, including real time flow queries to find the fastest queued hospitals in the vicinity, check hospital opening hours and dynamic announcements, it is convenient for users to plan their own medical treatment arrangement.

On-line consultation, home medical treatment, relieve the pressure of off-line medical treatment

The outbreak touched the hearts of all people, but also to ordinary patients with the inconvenience of seeking medical attention.

During the outbreak, to avoid cross-infection, experts advise people to quarantine as much as possible at home, some patients with minor illnesses are not advised to go to a large hospital. In this case, how to ensure that the epidemic does not delay the normal treatment of other diseases?

Online consultation offers people the possibility to go to the doctor at home.

During the outbreak, tencent, together with other major Internet medical service platforms such as Weiyi, good Doctor Online, Penguin Almond, the medical federation and Doctor Clove, joined tens of thousands of licensed doctors from all over the country, in response to the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, online free clinic services, including home protection, consultation advice and psychological consultation, are available through the online platforms tencent watch, tencent video and Wechat, to provide real-time authoritative online consulting services to the public, and help alleviate the pressure of offline hospitals.

Tencent provides online free clinic service with various Internet medical service platforms, such as Weiyi, good Doctor Online, Penguin Almond, iatrology, clove doctor, etc. .

It was revealed that most of these doctors from the third-class hospitals, using their spare time to online way to help the epidemic cloud. Many doctors have experience dealing with avian flu, seasonal flu, hand, foot and mouth infections, and even doctors dealt with SARS.

Behind every effective visit is an anxious individual, and every effective visit reduces the likelihood of a person going to the hospital to avoid a new cross infection with coronary pneumonia.

According to data provided by tencent, the outbreak occurred within 48 hours after the online free clinic service was launched, covering millions of users nationwide and answering hundreds of thousands of inquiries from users, helping to reduce the risk of cross-infection caused by improper offline consultation.

At present, users of online consultations are most concerned with identifying and preventing COVID-19. For example, how to prevent coronavirus infection, if a fever, dry cough, fatigue and other symptoms, whether it means that has been infected with a new coronavirus, COVID-19 what transmission methods.

On-line AI tools to improve the efficiency of self-examination of new coronary pneumonia

For the majority of users who have no obvious symptoms and no clear history of case contact, correct and scientific knowledge of new pneumonia prevention can be obtained through authoritative and professional epidemic science popularization and real-time rumor-refuting science popularization. Free online consultations are a new option for users who are uncertain about whether to seek medical advice offline, but are in urgent need of a doctor's professional advice. And to the user that needs off-line to see a doctor clearly, find right fever outpatient service or fixed-point admit a hospital is crucial in the first time.

When the service of on-line and off-line consultation is under pressure, the self-check products of artificial intelligence assume the function of providing more people with quick information, triage and medical guidance services.

On February 5, the Chinese Society of Preventive Medicine and tencent jointly launched the "new coronary pneumonia symptom AI self-examination tool" to help users who encounter symptoms such as fever and cough to quickly self-assess their condition and make reasonable medical arrangements.

It is understood that under the guidance of the Chinese Preventive Medicine Association, all the AI decision logic in the "new coronary pneumonia symptom AI assistant self-examination tool" has been examined by experts to ensure the reliability of AI assistant judgment. At the same time, experts will also participate in AI labeling to improve the accuracy of AI assisted judgment.

Tencent medical related officials said that from correct prevention of scientific investigation and popularization, to self-examination when suspected symptoms appear, to seeking professional advice from a volunteer doctor, to correctly seeking medical examination and fever clinic map, up to this point, tencent medical has developed a full-process decision-making tool for dealing with NCP online. Tencent medical expects that this complete online chain can act as a funnel to help the public provide timely information on medical and epidemic authorities, while at the same time, breaking down user needs layer by layer and addressing lighter needs online, finally, the heavy demand for off-line treatment will be quickly and accurately guided to the appropriate off-line hospital to help the hospital as much as possible to form accurate admission, save medical resources, improve the efficiency of allocation and use.

It offers convenient services and windows on the C side, and a fast access platform for tools on the B and g sides.

At present, tencent's "new pneumonia epidemic service platform" and various epidemic service tools have also served more than 40 health and disease control departments in 16 provinces, including Hubei, Guangdong, Beijing, Hunan, Shaanxi, Shandong, Henan, Hebei, Jiangsu, Anhui, Jiangxi, Jilin, Liaoning, Heilongjiang, Inner Mongolia, Qinghai and other provinces and cities, the public may enter the epidemic area through the corresponding wechat public number, small procedure and so on.

Tencent expressed the hope that this complete combination of online and offline and Wechat this social platform effectively combined to achieve a full and first touch of the masses.
